---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="Privacy Policy & Terms"
      description="Goodmood Privacy Policy and Terms of Use."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <div class="container page-wrap">

        <header class="page-header">
          <div class="section-label">Legal</div>
          <h1>Privacy Policy &amp; Terms of Use</h1>
          <p class="page-intro">Plain language. No surprises.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="legal-toc">
          <a href="#terms">Terms of Use</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="#privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
        </div>

        <div class="prose legal-prose">

          <!-- ── TERMS ── -->
          <h2 id="terms">Terms of Use</h2>
          <p class="last-updated">Last updated: May 1, 2026</p>

          <h3>Acceptance</h3>
          <p>
            By downloading or using Goodmood, you agree to these terms.
          </p>

          <h3>License</h3>
          <p>
            Goodmood grants you a personal, non-transferable, non-exclusive
            license to use the app on Apple devices you own or control, subject to the
            App Store Terms of Service.
          </p>

          <h3>Subscriptions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Goodmood Premium is available as a monthly or yearly auto-renewing subscription.</li>
            <li>Payment is charged to your Apple ID at confirmation of purchase.</li>
            <li>Subscriptions auto-renew unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
            <li>To cancel, go to <strong>Settings → [Your Name] → Subscriptions</strong>.</li>
            <li>No refunds are provided for partial subscription periods.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Permitted Use</h3>
          <p>
            You may use Goodmood for personal and professional purposes.
            You may not reverse-engineer, modify, or redistribute the app.
          </p>

          <h3>Disclaimer</h3>
          <p>
            Goodmood is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind.
            We are not liable for any damages arising from use of the app.
          </p>

          <h3>Governing Law</h3>
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which the
            developer is based.
          </p>

          <h3>Changes</h3>
          <p>
            We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the app
            constitutes acceptance.
          </p>

          <h3>Contact</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:hello@colorlenz.com">hello@colorlenz.com</a>
          </p>

          <hr />

          <!-- ── PRIVACY ── -->
          <h2 id="privacy">Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p class="last-updated">Last updated: May 1, 2026</p>

          <h3>What We Collect</h3>
          <p>
            Goodmood does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.
            The app captures your screen locally on your device solely to apply visual
            filters in real time. No screen content ever leaves your device.
          </p>

          <h3>Screen Recording Permission</h3>
          <p>
            Goodmood uses Apple's ScreenCaptureKit framework to read your display
            in real time, passes each frame through a GPU-accelerated color filter
            pipeline, and renders the result back to your screen as a transparent overlay.
          </p>
          <p>
            Frames are never written to disk, uploaded, or transmitted to any server.
            Everything happens in memory, on your device, in the moment. macOS requires
            Screen Recording permission for this kind of real-time display access — it
            is a technical requirement, not an indication that anything is being stored
            or shared.
          </p>

          <h3>The Companion (Optional Feature)</h3>
          <p>
            Goodmood includes an optional feature called the Companion — a friendly line
            that shows brief, encouraging, time-aware messages. It is turned off by default,
            and you can enable or disable it at any time in Settings.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Companion does not use Screen Recording. It never reads, captures, or
            analyzes the contents of your screen. It works entirely from your device's
            clock and, at most, the name of the app you currently have open — nothing more.
          </p>
          <p>When you choose to turn the Companion on:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Time-aware messages.</strong> Goodmood shows gentle greetings based on the time of day. This uses only your device's clock.</li>
            <li><strong>Activity awareness.</strong> To make messages more relevant, Goodmood reads the name of the application currently in the foreground (for example, your code editor, browser, or music app) using standard macOS APIs. This is used momentarily, on your device, only to choose a fitting message. It does not use Screen Recording, does not read your screen's contents, and does not access window titles, documents, or any personal information. The app name is never stored and never transmitted.</li>
            <li><strong>Optional name.</strong> If you enter your name, it is stored only on your device, in your local app preferences, so messages can address you personally. It is never transmitted. You can remove it at any time by clearing the field in Settings.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The Companion, including all of the above, runs entirely on your device.
            Nothing it processes is collected, stored off-device, or sent anywhere.
            When the Companion is turned off, none of this activity takes place.
          </p>

          <h3>Subscription &amp; Payments</h3>
          <p>
            Subscriptions are handled entirely by Apple via the App Store. We do not
            have access to your payment information. For billing inquiries, visit
            <strong>Settings → [Your Name] → Subscriptions</strong> on your device.
          </p>

          <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
          <p>
            We do not use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.
          </p>

          <h3>Children</h3>
          <p>
            Goodmood is not directed at children under 13. We do not
            knowingly collect data from children.
          </p>

          <h3>Changes</h3>
          <p>
            We may update this policy occasionally. Continued use of the app
            constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>

          <h3>Contact</h3>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:hello@colorlenz.com">hello@colorlenz.com</a>
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .page-wrap {
    max-width: 720px;
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-toc {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .legal-toc a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-subtle);
    margin-top: -0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 3rem 0 0.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-prose h3 {
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .legal-prose p {
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-prose ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-prose li {
    font-size: 0.93rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .legal-prose li::before {
    content: '–';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--text-subtle);
  }

  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .legal-prose strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .legal-prose hr {
    margin: 3rem 0;
  }
</style>
